article_node.title: Kenny Pickett on his hamstring, returning to Philadelphia, Shedeur Sanders, and more: Transcript
article_node.summary: Browns quarterback Kenny Pickett discussed his recovery from a hamstring injury and his experiences during joint practices with the Eagles, emphasizing the importance of competition and camaraderie. He praised teammates Quinyon Mitchell and Tanner McKee for their development and reflected on the challenges of managing injuries within a competitive quarterback landscape. Additionally, the article highlights the intense practice sessions between the Browns and Eagles, focusing on the performance of standout players like Myles Garrett, who continues to impress with his skills and work ethic.
